      "passage": "Deep sea organisms live in the darkest parts of the ocean, far below the reach of sunlight. Many of these animals create their own light through a chemical reaction inside their bodies. Some fish use glowing patches to attract small prey, while others use them to find a mate. Their bodies are often soft and flexible to handle the heavy pressure of deep water.",
