      "passage": "Early medicine relied on simple herbs and beliefs about the body's balance. Doctors in ancient Egypt mixed honey, salt, and crushed leaves to clean and dress wounds. Greek thinkers later argued that good health came from four fluids that had to stay in balance. Even with limited tools, many of their methods slowly improved over time and shaped later medical practice in Europe.",
